    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A name of convenience for a group of Persian rugs probably woven in Kirman at the beginning of the 17th century; motifs commonly include medallions, real and mythical animals, or human figures.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nombre convencional para un grupo de alfombras persas probablemente tejidas en Kirman a principios del siglo XVII; normalmente con diseños que incluyen medallones, animales reales y míticos o figuras humanas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Perzische tapijten die waarschijnlijk in het begin van de 17e eeuw in Kirman zijn geweven. De motieven in het ontwerp bevatten vaak medaillons, mythische en werkelijke dieren of menselijke gedaantes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052478/Kinebanian, Perzische en Oosterse tapijten</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>於十七世紀初期於克爾曼地區（Kirman）編織的一種波斯地毯，較常見的圖案有圓雕飾、真實或神話中的動物、或人像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
